The cybercrime of UPI (Unified Payment Interface) fraud is a common form of cybercrime in India, wherein the cybercriminal dupes the victim into transferring money or revealing sensitive information related to the bank account or the online payment system. The process of committing the cybercrime is as follows:
The cybercriminal establishes a sense of trust by using impressive and persuasive language. 
The cybercriminal sends a fake payment request or a malicious link to the victim, asking him or her to accept the request or enter the UPI PIN.
The cybercriminal tells the victim that he or she will be credited with money, but actually, the victim is tricked into paying the money.
The victim, after entering the PIN, loses the amount to the cybercriminal.
The victims of this cybercrime are college students, online shoppers, and those who are unaware of the digital payment system.
The consequences of the cybercrime include the loss of money, which can be recovered only after a long procedure.
The cybercrime of UPI fraud can be prevented by creating awareness among the users of digital payment platforms, as the victim should always remember that entering the PIN results in the approval of the payment, but the money is not credited to the account.
